    <caption>
      <p>Overview of capped small RNA-seq. (<italic>A</italic>) Schematic of short initiated RNAs that are captured by csRNA-seq and (<italic>B</italic>) a graphical depiction of the method starting from total RNA. (<italic>C</italic>) Transcription start site (TSS) clusters are determined through the enrichment of small capped RNAs over the total small RNA input using HOMER. The schematic shows the typical distribution of csRNA-seq and input at various genomic features. (<italic>D</italic>) Integration of genome annotations or total RNA-seq enables the assignment of TSSs to stable and unstable transcripts.</p>
